# Theme Token Colors Only

- Never use hardcoded colors in app code (`#hex`, `rgb()`, `hsl()`, inline style colors).
- Never use raw Tailwind palette color utilities for product UI surfaces/text (e.g. `bg-zinc-900`, `text-amber-300`) unless explicitly approved for one-off visualizations.
- Always use semantic token classes from `app/globals.css` (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `border-border`, `bg-cream-surface`, `text-ink-warm`).
- If a needed color does not exist, add a new CSS variable in `:root` and `.dark` in `app/globals.css`, expose it in `@theme inline`, then use that token class in components.
- Keep naming semantic and reusable (`cream-surface`, `ink-warm-muted`, `surface-strong`), not context-specific (`dashboard-card-bg`).

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid
<div className="bg-[#f1eadf] text-[#171717] border-[#e2d6c2]" />

// ✅ Use tokens
<div className="bg-cream-surface text-ink-warm border-cream-border" />
```
